description.p:
Simply stated, a* is a measure of how green or magenta the color is (since they are color opposites) and b* is a measure of how blue or yellow a color is.


From a mathematical perspective, a* and b* are determined as follows:


a*=500+(X/Xn)1/3 -(Y/Yn)1/3 }


b*=200+(Y/Yn)1/3 -(Z/Zn)1/3 }

R1 represents hydrogen or an alkyl group;


R2 represents an alkyl group or an aryl group;


n represents 1, 2, or 3;


each X is a substituent; and


Z represents a hydrogen atom or a group which can be split off by the reaction of the coupler with an oxidized color developing agent.
